  <amendments/>
  <summary>7/29/1987--Introduced.
Nuclear Regulatory Commission Accountability Act of 1987 - Amends the Energy Reorganization Act of 1974 to mandate that all Commission appointments shall be made from among persons who: (1) have filed a financial disclosure report for the two calendar years preceding such appointment; and (2) have not had a significant financial relationship with an entity subject to Commission regulation within the two-year period preceding such appointment. Prohibits former Commissioners from accepting compensation from a utility subject to the Commission's licensing jurisdiction during the two-year period beginning with separation from the Commission. Establishes civil penalties for violations of this Act.</summary>
